    "Body": " Position Description AVA's UI UX / Product Designer will contribute to the creation of amazing user experiences that define our products as highly attractive and competitive over incumbents. AVA Labs makes it simple to launch finance applications using blockchain technology-with highly scalable and efficient networks, customizable public and private blockchains, the capability to create any digital asset, and more. We are empowering people to build an open, simple, and democratic internet of finance. We are looking for someone who is keen on creating clean and artful design, and able to translate high-level requirements into interaction flows and artifacts, creating beautiful, intuitive, and functional user interfaces. Responsibilities Work together with product management and engineering to build innovative solutions for the product direction, visuals and experience Participate in all visual design stages from concept to final hand-off to engineering Develop original ideas that bring simplicity and user friendliness to complex design roadblocks Prepare wireframes, storyboards, user flows, process flows and site maps to effectively communicate interaction and design ideas Discuss designs and key milestone deliverables with peers and executive level stakeholders Perform user research and evaluate user feedback Set design guidelines, best practices and standards Stay up-to-date with the latest UI trends, techniques, and technologies What You'll Bring 2+ years' experience of working on a UI Designer position Interest in the cryptocurrency and blockchain space Solid understanding of UX deficiencies in blockchain applications Previous experience with payments application like Square, Paypal, or Venmo Significant experience in creating wireframes, storyboards, user flows, process flows, and site maps Significant experience with Photoshop, Illustrator, OmniGraffle, and other image editing and vector art tools Comfortable using tools like In-Design, Figma, and Zeplin to mockup and collaborate on design concepts Able to communicate with Front End engineers using HTML, CSS, and Javascript components. Able to execute business goals through proper design principles, testing, and automated user feedback tools. Comfortable presenting new designs to management staff for feedback and review Creative problem solver who is comfortable learning new techniques and technologies to improve their own productivity and workflow BS or MS degree in Human-Computer Interaction, Interaction Design, or other related area About AVA AVA Labs was founded by Cornell computer scientists who brought on talent from Wall Street to execute their vision. The company has received funding from Andreessen Horowitz, Initialized Capital, and Polychain Capital, with angel investments from Balaji Srinivasan and Naval Ravikant. https://www.avalabs.org/Show moreShow less ", 
